obs echo against the trees. The still fresh image of that elf sends two trails of tears down her rosey cheeks. He... He was the enemy. He was the one who needed to die. So why was he... kind? Burring her face in her arms, she lets her tears flow freely. The stress of the times had worn her thin and now, she would find at least some relief in the comforting whispers of the wind.<br>
