<br>
His attention quickly turned to the starting battle and soon he found one of the ends of his staff, jam hard against a Koada'Vie, the black energy that was the essence of the staff drove itself into the elf, causing a blood curtling scream, as though Undeen had just sent raw mana cursing through his body in a rather malicius fasion.  In truth, the only difference was the staff had done it for him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes!&quot; Undeen shouted at the barbarian as he struck down another charging Koada'dal, this one apparently not a Paladin.  Few of them remained, with the disapearance of the gods.  &quot;I'm Undeen.  What of it?&quot;<br>
<br>
His words finished, the Shadow Elf turned to the charging reinforcements of Koada'dal and gnomes and began to chant quickly, energy playing off his hands, and suddenly appearing amid the charging group, as a sudden, and outforcing blast of flames that engulfed many of the elves and gnomes, as well as the trees around them.<br>
<br>
Undeen turned to make sure the elf girl was alright, and beginning to wonder what was keeping the barbarian from answering, when he felt a sudden sting of pain, an arrow seeming to appear in his back, near his shoulder blade, nicely lodged between metal rings.<br>
<br>
With a shudder of pain, the blood beginning to flow out of the wound, Undeen turned himself back to the battle, standing himself between it and the girl.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> She may not be my little daughter, but someone has to be a father and protect her in this...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
(ooc: And so the battle rages on.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uzulik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zulik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Angel of Death</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/02 1:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: its high elf FIGHTIN TIME!!!!</span><hr size=1>  he slammed his foot into one high elves face   he saw the arrow hit the drow's back.<br>
