<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> This isn't going to be pretty.  Then again, war never is...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That thought in mind, Undeen began to chant quickly as he could, letting his arcane knowledge guide his tongue, his hands now beginning to reverberate with flashes of lightning.<br>
<br>
Aiming at what seemed to be the leader, Undeen lifts both hands which still held his staff, then let a flash of lightning-like energy pass off of him, striking down the apparent leader.<br>
<br>
&quot;Stand close if you are with me!  If you are against me, stay your hand and your feet, or meet a quick death at our hands!&quot;  His little line given, Undeen began the chant for a portal spell he had kept in his mind.  Soon all near him would find themselves in what was left of the forgotten valley, Kunark.  It was one of the few still safe places he could think of.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I just hope I was heard.  We'll see who here doesn't intend to kill me...  by all that's still pure, I'm going to have to rest after this...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
